AGC-LANG SYSTEM LANGUAGE
========================

AGC-LANG IS A SYSTEM PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE DESIGNED FOR KERNEL DEVELOPMENT WITH NATIVE EXECUTION CONTEXT SAFETY. IT ELIMINATES CLASSES OF KERNEL PANICS BY VERIFYING CONTEXT CONSTRAINTS AT COMPILE-TIME.

Quick start
-----------

REPORT A BUG: SEE AGC-LANG V1.0 SPECIFICATION.
GET THE LATEST SOURCE: STAGE-0 X86-64 NASM BOOTSTRAP.
BUILD THE COMPILER: SEE STAGE-1 SELF-HOSTING DOCUMENTATION.
JOIN THE COMMUNITY: ASM-FIRST DEVELOPMENT FOR SILICON-LEVEL CONTROL.

ESSENTIAL DOCUMENTATION
-----------------------

ALL USERS SHOULD BE FAMILIAR WITH:

BUILDING REQUIREMENTS: STAGE-0 NASM, MINIMAL ELF GENERATOR.
CONTEXT HIERARCHY: UNDERSTANDING IRQ_CTX, ATOMIC_CTX, AND PROCESS_CTX.
MEMORY SAFETY: UTILIZING BOND ALIASING ANALYSIS AND PULSE LEXICAL BLOCKS.
HARDWARE CONTROL: USING ZONE AND ANCHOR FOR MMIO AND DMA.
ERROR HANDLING: IMPLEMENTING ZERO-COST DRIFT AND ALIGN MECHANISMS.

DOCUMENTATION IS BASED ON THE AGC-LANG V1.0 SPEC.


WHO ARE YOU?
============

FIND YOUR ROLE BELOW:

NEW KERNEL DEVELOPER - GETTING STARTED WITH COMPILE-TIME CONTEXT SAFETY.
DRIVER ENGINEER - MANAGING HARDWARE REGISTERS VIA CORE BLOCKS AND REG BINDINGS.
SYSTEM ARCHITECT - DESIGNING SELF-HOSTING TOOLCHAINS WITH ZERO EXTERNAL DEPENDENCIES.
SECURITY EXPERT - HARDENING SYSTEMS THROUGH STATIC CFG AND BOND ANALYSIS.
HARDWARE VENDOR - WRITING HIGH-PERFORMANCE DRIVERS VIA NAKED FUNCTIONS.
MAINTAINER - ENFORCING CONTEXT PROPAGATION RULES AND CONSTRAINT MATRICES.
